						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Reducing-Postharvest-Losses-A-Challenge-for-the-Scientific-Community/Related-developments/GIS-helps-reduce-postharvest-loss-during-transportation" title="GIS helps reduce postharvest loss during transportation" alt="link">GIS helps reduce postharvest loss during transportation</a></h2>

	
					<p>A Ghanaian scientist designed a computer programme that combines satellite weather data and road conditions along different routes. Mixed into this are traffic information, ideal departure times and the number of (often illegal) stops. It is a recipe that prioritises speed, coolness and shade as well as smooth and level roads while also avoiding traffic jams, long border queues and checkpoints. Reduce spoilage would force the traders to pay the farmers more and sell the tomatoes for less. (<a href="http://gga.org/analysis/tomato-catch-up?utm_source=K4DNewsletterEN&amp;utm_medium=Link&amp;utm_campaign=K4D_EN_May2013" target="_self">Good Governance Africa</a>, 01/06/2013)</p>
							<p><span class="date">2/07/2013</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Reducing-Postharvest-Losses-A-Challenge-for-the-Scientific-Community/Related-developments/GIS-helps-reduce-postharvest-loss-during-transportation">Read more...</a>
