						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Reducing-Postharvest-Losses-A-Challenge-for-the-Scientific-Community/Related-developments/European-manufacturers-to-halve-food-waste-Australian-research-quantifies-food-waste" title="European manufacturers to halve food waste, Australian research quantifies food waste" alt="link">European manufacturers to halve food waste, Australian research quantifies food waste</a></h2>

	
					<p>Representatives from across Europeâ€™s food supply chain have committed their organizations to reducing edible food waste, in line with the European Commissionâ€™s goal of halving food waste &nbsp;by 2020. A life-cycle approach is being developed for critical products. In Australia, the study, titled â€˜The role of packaging in minimising food waste in the supply chain of the futureâ€™, from &nbsp;RMIT University in Melbourne focused on where and why food waste occurs both along the fresh and processed food supply. The research identifies opportunities for industry to address food &nbsp;waste through innovative and sustainable primary, secondary and tertiary packaging</p>
							<p><span class="date">31/07/2013</span></p>
