						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Reducing-Postharvest-Losses-A-Challenge-for-the-Scientific-Community/Related-developments/New-packaging-for-Tonga-s-agriculture-export-products" title="New packaging for Tongaâ€™s agriculture export products" alt="link">New packaging for Tongaâ€™s agriculture export products</a></h2>

	
					<p>The Pacific Horticultural and Agricultural Market Access Project (PHAMA), with the help of the New Zealand offices of Pacific Islands Trade &amp; Invest (PT&amp;I), developed new packaging &nbsp;material (retail plastic bags) and design (of label stickers) for Tongaâ€™s frozen root crop (cassava) products. Primarily meant to help producers meet market standards and compliance &nbsp;requirements in the New Zealand and Australian markets, the new labelling may well strengthen the competitive advantage of Tongaâ€™s agricultural export products. Four exporting companies &nbsp;have been selected to conduct the trial run of the packaging.(Pacific Periscope, 08/07/2013)</p>
							<p><span class="date">31/07/2013</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
